<paragraph id="7F3036F2FF84FFDEFF5FFBA6FEC0485D" blockId="19.[151,310,1124,1150]" box="[151,310,1124,1150]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<heading id="2478819EFF84FFDEFF5FFBA6FEC0485D" bold="true" box="[151,310,1124,1150]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" reason="1">
<emphasis id="4DFBEAE0FF84FFDEFF5FFBA6FEC0485D" bold="true" box="[151,310,1124,1150]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Tribe 
<taxonomicName id="B88F4D71FF84FFDEFF2AFBA6FEC0485D" authorityName="Bologna &amp; Amore &amp; Pitzalis" authorityYear="2018" box="[226,310,1124,1150]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Lyttini">Lyttini</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7F3036F2FF84FFDEFF5FFB68FDFE4971" blockId="19.[151,1436,1194,1363]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
According to morphological (Bologna &amp; Pinto 2001) and a preliminar molecular study (
<bibRefCitation id="1B1E4B03FF84FFDEFB50FB68FA7948E0" author="Bologna" box="[1176,1423,1194,1219]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refString="Bologna, M. A., Oliverio, M., Pitzalis, M. &amp; Mariottini, P. (2008 c) Phylogeny and evolutionary history of the blister beetles (Coleoptera, Meloidae). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 48, 679 - 693. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2008.04.019" type="journal article" year="2008" yearSuffix="c">
Bologna 
<emphasis id="4DFBEAE0FF84FFDEFACAFB69FACB48E1" box="[1282,1341,1194,1218]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
2008c
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="B88F4D71FF84FFDEFF5FFB0CFF1448C4" authorityName="Bologna &amp; Amore &amp; Pitzalis" authorityYear="2018" box="[151,226,1230,1255]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Lyttini">Lyttini</taxonomicName>
appear to be a polyphyletic group. Additional molecular studies actually support the monophyly of the tribe with the inclusion of some genera referred to other tribes (Bologna 
<emphasis id="4DFBEAE0FF84FFDEFC4EFB31FC484929" box="[902,958,1266,1290]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
unpublished). In the present catalogue, we consider in this tribe the genera previously referred to 
<taxonomicName id="B88F4D71FF84FFDEFD37FAD4FCBC490C" authorityName="Bologna &amp; Amore &amp; Pitzalis" authorityYear="2018" box="[767,842,1302,1327]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Lyttini">Lyttini</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="1B1E4B03FF84FFDEFCBEFAD4FBD1490C" author="Bologna" box="[886,1063,1302,1327]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refString="Bologna, M. A. (1991) Coleoptera Meloidae. Fauna d'Italia. XXVIII. Calderini, Bologna, XIV + 541 pp." type="book" year="1991">Bologna (1991)</bibRefCitation>
and by 
<bibRefCitation id="1B1E4B03FF84FFDEFB4BFAD4FA6E490C" author="Bologna" box="[1155,1432,1302,1327]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refString="Bologna, M. A. &amp; Pinto, J. D. (2002) The Old World genera of Meloidae (Coleoptera): a key and synopsis. Journal of Natural History, 36, 2013 - 2102. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930110062318" type="journal article" year="2002">Bologna &amp; Pinto (2002)</bibRefCitation>
, with the addition of 
<taxonomicName id="B88F4D71FF84FFDEFEB2FAF8FDF74971" authorityName="Peringuey" authorityYear="1909" box="[378,513,1338,1362]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Cyaneolytta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DFBEAE0FF84FFDEFEB2FAF8FDF74971" box="[378,513,1338,1362]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Cyaneolytta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
